data.current_summary: Retrieve a list of versions of specified (or all) feeds.
data.current_description: This API call allows you to easily see every single feed update in the TranstiFeeds.com system. Since this can be quite long, it's also possible to filter this list by a single feed ID.
data.summary_suggestion: List feed versions with optional filtering by feed ID
data.description_suggestion: Retrieves all feed versions available in the TransitFeeds system, optionally filtered by a specific feed ID. Useful for tracking feed update history and identifying specific versions for download. Supports pagination parameters to manage large result sets.

data.current_summary: Retrieve the download URL for the latest version of a feed.
data.current_description: Once you have used `/getFeeds` to discover a feed's URL, you can use this endpoint to download its latest version from TranstiFeeds. It will be unmodified in the original format from the provider.
data.summary_suggestion: Get the latest feed version download URL
data.description_suggestion: Retrieves the latest version of a specified feed from TransitFeeds. Returns a GetLatestFeedVersionResponse containing the FeedVersion object with download URL, version metadata, and timestamp. The feed data is provided unmodified in its original format from the provider. Requires a valid feed ID obtained from `/getFeeds`. Use this endpoint to access the most current transit data for a feed.
